stories.storyDescription: Jennifer: Can we do this tomorrow? I’ve had my fill of emotional turmoil for the night.
I could feel my face going red again, and I lowered my eyes, embarrassed.

stories.storyDescription: I was almost sorry when the eight hour drive ended and we pulled up into my parents’ driveway.
Twenty-five years of marriage and they were still like teenagers.

Luke nodded and lowered his hands, letting me continue where I’d left off.
